1 System of Higher Education of the policies developed
2 pursuant to this paragraph, and
3 d. the extent to which professors and other faculty and
4 students at institutions within The Oklahoma State
5 System of Higher Education may acquire property
6 interests in technology developed on the premises of
7 or with the assistance of an institution within The
8 Oklahoma State System of Higher Education or a
9 property interest in the revenues derived by the sale,
10 marketing, licensing, or other disposition of
11 technology by an institution within The Oklahoma State
12 System of Higher Education or by a private business
13 entity conducting research or engaged in the
14 development of technology on the premises of or with
15 the assistance of an institution within The Oklahoma
16 State System of Higher Education. The policy shall
17 include a tiered system of ownership based on the
18 amount of revenue generated from the new technology.
19 The policy shall also ensure that the inventor or
20 discoverer is compensated competitively to similarly
21 situated institutions; and
22 2. Establish policies for institutions within The Oklahoma
23 State System of Higher Education to:
